summary: I know there’s been a lot of debate on here and other sites over whether or not Phan is real and if they’re secretly together or...
body:
I know there’s been a lot of debate on here and other sites over whether or not Phan is real and if they’re secretly together or if they’re just close friends, so I thought I’d add my input into the controversy and tell you my story of my personal experience with irl shipping. 

The phandom is not a place that I like to share my opinion because I know so many of the phannies are very opinionated and get very offended when someone says they don’t ship phan, but idk I feel like I have to share this.

My friend and I have been really close best friends since we were about 11 or 12. We’re as close as two people can get without dating, we text each other nonstop all day, and I swear to god sometimes I think we can read each other’s minds, it’s kind of scary. 

But the problem with our friendship is, 2 years into it, people started romantically shipping us together. 

In the beginning I think it was more funny because people thought we’d be a cute couple since I’m a foot taller than her, but as the years progressed, it definitely got more serious and weird. At the peak of it one person actually wrote fanfiction about us [which I think has been taken down] and some people in our school actually thought we were dating. 

Now, for clarification, she’s straight and I’m not, so I think she was more annoyed than I was at it but it bothered us. Usually she keep quiet about it in public it but I would react to it right there. 

A few of my friends do still ship us [and probably like to believe we’re dating] but other than that it’s not as popular as it was a few years ago. Me and my friend are still super duper best friends for life, and I think that the whole thing with people shipping us actually brought us closer in a way, which I am grateful for. But it was still weird. 

So, in a way, me and my friend can kind of relate to Dan and Phil in the sense that we know how uncomfortable it can be when people almost force you into a situation you don’t want to/can’t be in, even if our experience with it wasn’t as hectic and crazed as theirs is. 

This is why I usually don’t interfere in the “Is Phan real?” debate because I can see how they find it annoying. If they were actually together, would I be happy for them? Yeah. But if they were to just stay as friends would I be fine with that too? Of course. I’m just happy to wait for their new content and watch their old videos in peace. 

I think that’s all I have to say. I know no one will bother to read this but whatever, I thought this needed to be shared.
